external_knowledge:
- "Significant gap" refers to a difference greater than 10 points;
- The "average grade of the course" is the mean final grade of all students in that course;
- The "average grade of the students" is the mean final grade of all courses taken by each student.

- 'Fall 2023' refers to the academic semester starting in September 2023 and ending in December 2023;
- 'final grade' is the overall grade calculated for the course;
- 'average assessment grade' is the mean grade of all assessments taken by the student in the semester;
- 'average course rating' is the mean rating given by the student for the courses they took in the semester.

- "Tended by faculty gardeners" refers to courses advised by faculty members;
- "Blossomed with an average final grade above 70" means the average final grade of the course is greater than 70;
- "Average course rating above 3" means the average rating given to the course is greater than 3.

sql:
SELECT evaluation_text, instructor_rating
FROM course_evaluations
WHERE instructor_rating > 3 AND course_rating > 3;

external_knowledge:
- 'Mathematical scholars' refers to students majoring in Mathematics;
- 'Planted their seeds of knowledge in the garden of academia after the dawn of 2020' refers to students who enrolled after 2020;
- 'Average growth' refers to the average grade of students;
- 'Foundational course' refers to the course with course_id = 1.

sql:
SELECT course_id, MAX(final_grade) AS max_final_grade
FROM final_grades
GROUP BY course_id;
